    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.12-13_0001"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 24</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Daddy just came home bringing the good news that you will visit us next week. Daddy said that he did not write of any plans except the visit to the Harry Truman Library on Thursday at ten, so he asked me to send you further details.</p>
                
                <p>Since Daddy is sitting on the bench in Independence this week, your telegram was read over the phone to his clerk so we may not be clear on your plans. Since he believes you are driving here, I will give you directions. At Blue Springs, Highway 7 intersects Highway 40.
                
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.12-13_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">2.</fw>
                
                    There is a light there. Turn left on 7 and go about 5 miles where there is a blinker light and continue on 7 for about 2 more miles, perhaps a little less. On the left hand side of the road, after you pass the blinker light, you will pass Gates 3, 4 and 5. Then there is quite a distance to Gate 6. Turn left at this Gate and you come to a <hi rend="caps">T</hi> and take the left road. After a short ways the road branches into a <hi rend="caps">Y</hi> and again you take the left road. It leads to the Lake Road and there you make the only right turn. You are at
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.12-13_0001a"/>
                
                    R-37 when you enter the Lake Road and we live at R-10.</p>
                
                <p>If convenient, come any time on Wednesday. We hope some of your family can come with you. They would be most welcome.</p>
                
                <p>If we are mistaken and you are coming by plane on train be sure to let us know so we may meet you. Our phone number at Lake Lotawana is Prospect 4-3393. Daddy said he gave you the Court House number.</p>
                
                <p>I am looking forward with great pleasure to your visit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lyn</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
